Acceptance Criteria:

A Spring Batch job is defined in the service module.

The job includes steps for:

Reading data from the fixed-length file.

Mapping the data to a Fileload entity or a staging entity.

Writing the data to the staging table using Spring JDBC or JPA.

The job configuration handles:

File input source.

File parsing (fixed-length format).

Data mapping.

Database writing.

Error handling (skip policies, retry policaes).

Transaction management.

The job updates the FileLoad entity with the load status and record count.

